The paper deals with a variant of index coding problem and provides index codes for different cases. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) and network communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses a class of PICOD where the side information is consecutive, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper introduces a variant of PICOD with a c-constraint, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and computer networks (cs.NI). However, since the paper focuses more on the theoretical aspects of the problem, it is less likely to belong to the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
